    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="713"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.9111 RR/4–1649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-16">April 16,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received April 17—2:48 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 223. Chinese Press. UP report Pacification Commander Yu Han-mou has
                    prevented shipment silver by Central Bank from Canton to interior China. <hi
                        rend="italic">Kung Ping Pao</hi> (C–C Clique<note n="51" xml:id="d713fn51"
                        >Group in the Kuomintang led by Chen Li-fu and Chen Kuo-fu.</note>) carried
                    extra April 14 covering story. According UP, Kwangtung garrison troops April 14
                    prevented loading, approximately 7 tons silver aboard chartered CATC<note n="52"
                        xml:id="d713fn52">Central Air Transport Corporation.</note> plane. Silver
                    returned vaults Central Bank; frozen by military decree. Central Bank official
                    stated shipment ordered National Finance Minister; destined Liuchow for shipment
                    this week, via 6 chartered CAT[C] planes. UP states understood Central Bank
                    already shipped $200,000 before military action. Military states action taken
                    prevent further local inflation. According UP, news proposed shipment forced up
                    local price silver dollar parity with US dollar.</p>
                <p>Sent Department; repeated Nanking 198, Shanghai 144.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
